16/11/2005
PARIS, France -- President Jacques Chirac met with Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader on Tuesday (15 November) and reassured him of France's continued support for Croatia's EU aspirations.
After the meeting, Sanader told reporters that Chirac supports admitting Croatia before 2009, and plans to send one of France's most experienced diplomats -- former European Commission official Guy Legras -- to Zagreb as an adviser.
In other news Tuesday, Croatian Foreign and EU Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic addressed the OSCE Permanent Council in Vienna about Croatia's progress in meeting international obligations.
Afterwards, the British presidency of the EU praised the level of co-operation between Croatia and the OSCE Mission to Zagreb.
(HINA, EU Web site, OSCE Web site - 15/11/05)
